  The SI second = exactly 9,192,631,770 oscillations of the
  cesium-133 hyperfine transition.

    Cesium frequency dv_Cs (Hz)            9192631770.0
    dv_Cs is exact (SI definition)         9192631770.0
    Cycles per 'second'                    9192631770.0
    Hydrogen 1S-2S frequency (Hz)          2.4660614132e+15
    H/Cs frequency ratio                   268265.00559

  The hydrogen atom oscillates 268265.0× faster than cesium.
  This is not 'time passing faster.' It is a DIFFERENT VORTEX
  with a different internal process rate.

  Every 'clock' is a vortex. What it 'measures' is its own
  oscillation count. The count depends on the vortex's structure
  and its position in the soliton hierarchy.
  [PASS] Cesium frequency is exact SI definition
        dv_Cs = 9192631770.0

